==English==
===Etymology===
Shortened from "[[cup]] [[o']] (of) [[tea]]", with -a replacing o'.

===Noun===
'''cuppa''' (''plural'' '''cuppas''')

#(''British colloquial'') A cup of tea.
#:''I've just put the kettle on - fancy a cuppa?''

